DAY RF PSB

psbop@CWO-CCC-B2LC
A thought occurred over the weekend for the blow-up. It might be the case that if I rotate the phase of C16 using the relevant knob I can get it to the same relative phase in all 4 rings allowing for (roughly) the same blow-up parameters.

What I will do is first duplicate the settings from R3 and then rotate the phase and see what the effect is on the beam.

24/07/2017 10:45

DAY RF PSB

psbop@CWO-CCC-B2LC
Phase offset on its own is not *quite* sufficient, I am guessing that C04 might be causing a slight shift in the frequency spread, causing the core to be at a slightly different frequency in the two rings.

I'm first going to see if small changes to the modulation frequency is enough to compensate for the synchrotron frequency.

Modulation frequency sweep didn't help, trying C16 voltage. No meaningful effect, expected but good to see.

C04 phase definitely having a strong effect, this was exactly what I was hoping wouldn't be the case. Damn.

SA
24/07/2017 11:57

DAY RF PSB

psbop@CWO-CCC-B2LC
Sloshing back and forth between C04 phase and C16 phase I have been able to get a beautifully shaped bunch, but the emittance is 0.2 eVs too low. I've pushed up the C16 voltage a bit but it doesn't quite compensate enough.

SA

DAY RF PSB

psbop@CWO-CCC-B2LC

Checking reproducibility and I'm happy with it. 5 Sequential shots has 1.49 -> 1.52 eVs emittances.
